org.ensor.math.geometry

Interface IVector<VectorType>

  • Type Parameters:
    VectorType - The concrete type of the vector.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDifferentiableFunction<VectorType>, IVectorWithNorm<VectorType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConstantFunction, CubicFunction, LinearFunction, QuadraticFunction, Vector2, Vector3, Vector4

    public interface IVector<VectorType>
    This interface represents an element of a vector space. The element assumes that the field 'F' of the vector space is the real numbers (as represented approximately by a double).
    Author:
    jona
